{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641193"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:24:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:24:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17870"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17870","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17870"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.19,0.1,0.19,0.43]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10584"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78688"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10584","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10584"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17870"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64031"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24671"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24676"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78688","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78688"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following locations in skeletal muscle stores fat in discrete lipid droplets?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inter-myofibrillar","Intra-myofibrillar","Subsarcolemmal","Perinuclear","Perimysial"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESkeletal muscle stores fat in discrete lipid droplets primarily within the \u003Cstrong\u003Einter-myofibrillar\u003C/strong\u003E space. This area is located between the myofibrils, which are the contractile elements of muscle cells. The inter-myofibrillar space is rich in mitochondria and is a key site for energy metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntra-myofibrillar\u003C/strong\u003E refers to within the myofibrils themselves, which is not a  site for lipid storage. Myofibrils are primarily composed of actin and myosin filaments responsible for muscle contraction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubsarcolemmal\u003C/strong\u003E lipid droplets are located just beneath the cell membrane (sarcolemma) of muscle cells, but they are not the primary site for lipid storage in skeletal muscle.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerinuclear\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the area surrounding the nucleus, which is not a common site for lipid storage in muscle cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerimysial\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the connective tissue surrounding bundles of muscle fibers, which is not involved in lipid storage within muscle cells.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Skeletal muscle stores fat in discrete lipid droplets within the inter-myofibrillar space.","The inter-myofibrillar space is the area between the myofibrils in muscle cells."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Chandel NS. Lipid Metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Sep 1;13(9):a040576. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a040576. PMID: 34470787; PMCID: PMC8411952","Wakil SJ, Abu-Elheiga LA. Fatty acid metabolism: target for metabolic syndrome. J Lipid Res. 2009 Apr;50 Suppl(Suppl):S138-43. doi: 10.1194/jlr.R800079-JLR200. Epub 2008 Dec 1. PMID: 19047759; PMCID: PMC2674721"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"6